            "body": "~Yes, Vim sets `background` correctly.\nI believe Vim does it on the `set_tty_background` function that was removed from Neovim in favor of `TermResponse` autocmds.~\n\nNot actually, Vim's default colorscheme has no background color and that mislead me to think it set `background` correclty.\nBoth Neovim and Vim doesn't set the background correctly on `Windows Terminal + powershell`, but on `Windows Terminal + WSL + fish` Vim sets background correctly and Neovim doesn't.",
