            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Check your Windows Terminal settings. There are three settings that control how the background color behaves. Each successive one can override the previous one(s).\n\n1. **Appearance**, **Application Theme** = [Dark | Light | Use Windows Theme]\n1. **Profiles**, **Defaults**, **Appearance**, **Color scheme**\n1. **Profiles**, *{my profile}*, **Appearance**, **Color scheme**\n\nNeovim's background detection appears to be tied to the 1st setting, no matter which color scheme is chosen for the profiles. If you select \"Use Windows Theme\", you can also specify both a light and a dark color scheme for your profiles. You'll have to edit the JSON file to make that change. See https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/terminal/customize-settings/profile-appearance#color-scheme for instructions.",
